[A few words about the elephant in the El Nino room. It is entirely
possible that all deaths in humans, animals and some plants will be
attributed to El Nino in some way for the forseeable future. In this case,
it is not difficult to see a clear causal pathway between increased
rainfall, more mosquitos and a 25% or greater increase in malaria.
Furthermore, this is a newspaper report and we can't expect the
establishment of causal pathways from such sources. However, I think
discussions about the effects of El Nino should have strict demarcations
between speculation concerning dislocations caused by El Nino and proven
effects of El Nino. While I don't doubt the substantial increase in the La
Convencion malaria problem may be due to climatic sources, I would like to
see data establishing the causal linkages. - Mod. pc]
